31/08/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A total of 17,882 people are still missing from conflicts in the former Yugoslavia in the 1990s, Paul Henri Arni, head of the International Red Cross in Belgrade said on Thursday (August 30th). 
The majority, 13,500 of them, disappeared during the 1992-1995 conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina, compared to 2,386 in the 1991-1995 conflict in Croatia and 2,047 in the 1998-1999 strife in Kosovo. 
The findings were released to mark the International Day of the Disappeared. 
(SRNA, Makfax, Focus, AP, UPI - 30/08/07)
